<TEXT>
   Here are the members of the National Association
of State Boards of Education task force which produced ``Right From
The Start: The Report of the NASBE Task Force on Early Childhood
Education.''
   Roy Blunt, Secretary of State, Missouri;
   Dodie Truman Borup, U.S. Commissioner for Children, Youth &amp;
Families;
   Barbara Bowman, Director of Graduate Studies, Erikson Institute,
Chicago;
   Richard Boyd, Superintendent of Education, Mississippi;
   Mary Busch, member, Indianapolis School Board;
   Maria Chavez, member, New Mexico State Board of Education;
   Hillary Rodham Clinton, First Lady of Arkansas;
   Michael Cowper, First Lady of Alaska;
   Carolyn Cummings, early childhood consultant, Saginaw, Mich.,
Public Schools;
   Barbara Day, professor and chair of teaching and learning,
University of North Carolina;
   David Elkind, professor of child study, Tufts University;
   Ethel Hall, member, Alabama State Board of Education;
   Rebecca Pena Hines, assistant director, University of Texas Child
Care Center;
   Sharon Lynn Kagan, associate director, Bush Center in Child
Development, Yale University;
   Donna Kenney Moffat, Buffalo preschool teacher, New York State
Teacher of the Year;
   Gwen Morgan, lecturer, Wheelock College in Boston;
   Richard Owens, NASBE president, member of Georgia State Board of
Education;
   Gary Patterson, director, Early Childhood Interagency Committee,
South Carolina;
   Lee Etta Powell, superintendent, Cincinnati public schools;
   Gregory Ross, president, Children's World Learning Centers,
Golden, Colo.;
   Donnetta Spink, chair, National PTA Education Commission;
   State Rep. Kaye Steinmetz of Missouri;
   Jule Sugerman, secretary for social and health services,
Washington State;
   Bernice Weissbourd, president, Family Focus, Evanston, Ill.
   Elizabeth Strong Ussery, associate commissioner, Head Start
Bureau;
   State Assemblywoman Cathy Zeuske of Wisconsin.
</TEXT>
